<div id="dw-summary-article">

<div class="dw-content-head">
<h1>Second Life client, Part 1: Hacking Second Life</h1><p><em>Set up a Second Life development environment</em></p>
</div>

<div class="ibm-container-body ibm-two-column">

<div class="ibm-column ibm-first">
<div class="author"><a class="dwauthor" rel="#authortip1" href="#author1">Peter Seebach</a> (<a href="mailto:developerworks@seebs.plethora.net?subject=Hacking Second Life">developerworks@seebs.plethora.net</a>), Freelance writer, Plethora.net</div><div id="authortip1" class="dwauthor-onload-state ibm-no-print"><div class="position"><img src="http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/i/p-seebach.jpg" width="64" height="80" alt="Author photo" /></div>Peter Seebach has been using computers for years and is gradually becoming acclimated. He still doesn't know why mice need to be cleaned so often, though.</div>
<p></p>
<p><b>Summary:</b>&nbsp; The open source release of the Second Life viewer program by
      developer Linden Lab offers a rare opportunity to peer into the comparative
      strengths of closed and open source development models. This article, the first in a
            <a href="http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/views/linux/libraryview.jsp?topic_by=All+topics+and+related+products&amp;sort_order=asc&amp;lcl_sort_order=asc&amp;search_by=second+life+client%2C&amp;search_flag=true&amp;type_by=Articles&amp;show_abstract=true&amp;start_no=1&amp;sort_by=Title&amp;end_no=100&amp;show_all=false&amp;S_TACT=105AGX03&amp;S_CMP=EDUp;show_abstract=true&amp;sort_by=Relevance&amp;end_no=100&amp;show_all=false" onmouseover="linkQueryAppend(this)">series</a> gives an overview of some of the differences between these development
      styles, and talks about what's involved in setting up your own build environment.</p>
<p class="ibm-no-print"><a href="http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/views/linux/libraryview.jsp?topic_by=All+topics+and+related+products&amp;sort_order=asc&amp;lcl_sort_order=asc&amp;search_by=second+life+client%2C&amp;search_flag=true&amp;type_by=Articles&amp;show_abstract=true&amp;start_no=1&amp;sort_by=Title&amp;end_no=100&amp;show_all=false&amp;S_TACT=105AGX03&amp;S_CMP=EDUp;show_abstract=true&amp;sort_by=Relevance&amp;end_no=100&amp;show_all=false">View more content in this series</a></p>
<div id="dw-tag-content" class="ibm-no-print"></div><div id="dw-moretags-access" class="ibm-access"></div>
<p class="ibm-no-print"><div id="dw-tag-this" class="ibm-no-print"><a class="ibm-external-link" onclick="jQuery.launchTagThisWindow(); return false;" href="#">Tag this!</a></div><div id="interestShow" class="ibm-no-print"></div></p>
</div>

<div class="ibm-column ibm-second">
<p class="leading"><b>Date:</b>&nbsp; 27 Mar  2007
<br /><b>Level: </b>&nbsp;Intermediate

<br /><b>Also available in:&nbsp;</b>
&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/cn/linux/l-second-life-1.html">Chinese</a>


&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/jp/linux/library/l-second-life-1.html">Japanese</a> 



<br />
<br /><b>Activity:</b>&nbsp; 24656 views
<br /><b>Comments:</b> &nbsp; <span id="nCmts"><img alt="" src="//dw1.s81c.com/developerworks/i/circle-preloader.gif" height="12" width="50" /><img alt="" src="//dw1.s81c.com/i/c.gif" height="14" width="1" /></span>
